STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. EDDIE JAMES BAITEY, Appellant. STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. MATTHEW JENKINS WILLIAMS, Appellant. (No. 41668, consol.) 510 P2d 360 J. Marvin Kuhn, Deputy Public Defender, Salem, argued the cause for appellants. With him on the brief was Gary D. Babcock, Public Defender, Salem. Thomas E. Denney, Assistant Attorney General, Salem, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief were Lee Johnson, Attorney General, and John W. Osbum, Solicitor General, Salem.

Argued May 24,

affirmed May 24,

petition for rehearing denied June 14,

petition for review denied September 5, 1973

Before Schwab, Chief Judge, and Port and Thornton, Judges.
